    "causal_summary": "Figma Desktop holds a project's real design systems, tokens, variables, and components, but a coding agent could only reach them through the Figma UI or a remote-API workflow. Whether and how Figma can be driven from a terminal was unknown, and the npm registry carries a naming trap: the package literally named `figma-cli` is an unrelated tool (unic/figma-cli), while the capability the framework wanted lives in the silships figma-cli, published as `figma-ds-cli`. The Figma MCP landscape (first-party and community) also needed an honest survey before committing to a skill design.",
